[4] Indonesia
Date: Tue 30 Jan 2007
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: Bernama.com, Malaysian National News Agency [edited]
<http://www.bernama.com.my/bernama/v3/news.php?id=244122>

A total of 4862 dengue fever cases with 75 of them ending in the
patient's death have been recorded in January [2007] alone in
Indonesia, according to the Health Ministry report.
The cases occurred in 14 of the country's 33 provinces with the
special region of Jakarta registering the highest figure, Dr. Erna
Tresnaningsih, the head of the ministry's directorate of animal-borne
disease control, said.
Jakarta has the highest number of dengue fever patients, followed by
West Java, Central Java, and Lampung on Sumatera Island, she said,
and added that in December 2006, a total of 5400 dengue fever cases
were reported in 28 provinces leading to 77 deaths.
In January 2006 [2007? Mod. TY] the number of cases reached 18 941 in
33 provinces and led to 192 deaths, she said.
The health ministry had taken several measures to reduce the rate of
fatalities from the disease that always spreads before and after the
rainy season through the _Aedes aegypti_ mosquito. "The key to its
prevention is the environment and the people. If the environment is
free of pools of water which can be used by the mosquito to breed and
the people maintain environmental health, the disease is surely more
controllable," Tresnaningsih said as quoted by the Antara news agency
Tuesday [30 Jan 2007]. She admitted that efforts to control the
disease had not yielded the desired results because public
participation was still relatively low.
Meanwhile in West Java, a total of 42 people have died in the
outbreak of dengue fever in the province since early this month
{January 2007]. The province recorded 1889 confirmed cases of dengue
fever between 1 and 29 Jan [2007], said Dr. Yudhi Prayudha, Head of
the Provincial Health Office, adding that the number of deaths rose
sharply from only 27 in the same period last year [1-29 Jan 2006]
mostly because the patients sought medical treatment only at a very late stage.
[Byline Mohd Nasir Yusoff]
